tedious /ˈtiːdɪəs/

1. ADJ If you describe something such as a job, task, or situation as tedious , you mean it is boring and frustrating. 乏味烦人的 

例： Such lists are long and tedious to read. 这种清单读起来既冗长又乏味烦人。 

2. tediously ADV 乏味烦人地 

例： ...the most tediously boring aspects of international relations. …国际关系中最乏味烦人的某些方面。

